    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of shrub native to central and southern Europe, northwest Africa and western Asia, naturalized in northern Europe and North America. The seeds and berries are used for food; other parts of the plant are both mildly poisonous and medicinal. The bark has been used as a raw material for a natural dye.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
